text: Seamus Ó hÉilidhe (Anglicised: James O'Hely, died 1595) was an Irish Roman Catholic clergyman. He was appointed Archbishop of Tuam by the Holy See on 20 March 1591, and died in office in 1595. ==References== Category:1595 deaths Category:16th-century Irish people Category:People from County Mayo Category:People from County Galway Category:Roman Catholic archbishops of Tuam Category:Year of birth unknown
